# Studio Build (Embedded Assets)

Studio UI is built into `internal/studio/dist` and embedded by Go (`go:embed`). Source changes alone do **not** update the binary assets.

## When required

After any change under `studio/` (source, tests that affect the app build, dependencies, or Studio build config such as `package.json`, `vite.config.*`, `pnpm-lock.yaml`, `pnpm-workspace.yaml`), **before** marking the task done:

```sh
make studio-build
git status --short internal/studio/dist
```

## Definition of done for Studio changes

- [ ] `make studio-build` succeeded
- [ ] Generated updates under `internal/studio/dist` are present in the working tree / final diff when the build produces them (do not discard or unstage them)
- [ ] If the build fails, the task is incomplete — fix the build; do not skip asset regeneration

Studio lint/typecheck/unit tests remain optional based on change risk; the embed rebuild is **not** optional when Studio sources changed.
